---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Bell Environmental Alternative NYC | Cloakd"
  description="Bell Environmental's multilayer defense eliminates what's there. The replacement colony that forms four weeks later is a biology problem their program isn't designed to address."
  path="/vs/bell-environmental"
>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── HERO ── -->
  <section class="pt-20 pb-24 px-6 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-6">
        Bell Environmental vs. Cloakd
      </p>
      <h1 class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-[1.08] tracking-tight mb-8">
        Bell Environmental's multilayer defense removes what's there.<br />
        Here's what keeps the problem coming back.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-[#1c1814]/70 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        Bell Environmental has been serving NYC metro commercial clients
        since 1963. Their multilayer program — perimeter protection plus
        internal mechanical trapping — is a sound approach to eliminating
        active rodent populations. The replacement cycle that refills empty
        territory after elimination is outside what any mechanical trapping
        program addresses. That's the gap fertility management closes.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── WHAT BELL COVERS ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-[#f0ebe0]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        What Bell Environmental's program covers
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-6 max-w-2xl">
        Sixty years of NYC commercial pest control. Same biological limitation as every standard program.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-start">
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed">
            Bell Environmental's Zero-Pest Zone System covers the full
            perimeter of a commercial building — outside protection combined
            with internal mechanical trapping to eliminate Norway rats and
            mice across all five NYC boroughs. Their licensed pest management
            professionals serve restaurants, hotels, hospitals, and commercial
            properties throughout the NYC metro area.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed">
            The issue isn't the program — it's what happens after the
            population is removed. Mechanical trapping reduces the active
            colony. It doesn't reduce the fertility of the replacement
            population moving in from surrounding harborage once the
            territory goes empty. Four to eight weeks after a successful
            elimination, the same travel paths, the same entry points,
            the same food sources produce the same infestation.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed">
            For NYC restaurant operators on a recurring DOHMH inspection
            cycle, that replacement timeline is the exposure. Fertility
            management doesn't replace Bell's mechanical program — it
            addresses the one variable that program can't reach.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4">
          {[
            {
              label: 'What Bell Environmental covers',
              items: [
                'Perimeter protection — outside building rodent defense',
                'Internal mechanical trapping program',
                'Zero-Pest Zone System Guarantee',
                'Licensed PMP service across all five NYC boroughs and NJ',
                'DOHMH compliance documentation',
              ],
              positive: true,
            },
            {
              label: 'What mechanical trapping leaves open',
              items: [
                'Replacement colony forming after mechanical elimination',
                'Population fertility during the interval between visits',
                'Documented 90-day population trend for DOHMH inspectors',
                'Track count data showing activity trajectory over time',
              ],
              positive: false,
            },
          ].map(({ label, items, positive }) => (
            <div class={`rounded-xl p-6 ${positive ? 'bg-white border border-[#1c1814]/8' : 'bg-white border border-[#c96a3a]/15'}`}>
              <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-[#1c1814]/45 mb-4">{label}</p>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                {items.map((item) => (
                  <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                    <div class={`w-5 h-5 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center mt-0.5 ${positive ? 'bg-[#7aab7e]/15' : 'bg-[#1c1814]/8'}`}>
                      {positive
                        ? <svg width="10" height="8" viewBox="0 0 10 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 4L3.5 6.5L9 1" stroke="#5e9263" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
                        : <svg width="8" height="8" viewBox="0 0 8 8" fill="none"><path d="M1 1L7 7M7 1L1 7" stroke="#1c1814" stroke-opacity="0.3" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
                      }
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/70 leading-relaxed">{item}</p>
                  </div>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── COMPARISON TABLE ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        Side-by-side comparison
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-12 max-w-2xl">
        Bell Environmental vs. Cloakd 90-day program
      </h2>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b border-[#1c1814]/10">
              <th class="py-4 pr-6 text-sm font-semibold text-[#1c1814]/45 uppercase tracking-widest w-1/3">Feature</th>
              <th class="py-4 pr-6 text-sm font-semibold text-[#1c1814]/45 uppercase tracking-widest w-1/3">Bell Environmental</th>
              <th class="py-4 text-sm font-semibold text-[#c96a3a] uppercase tracking-widest w-1/3">Cloakd (added layer)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {[
              ['Treatment method', 'Perimeter defense + internal mechanical trapping (Zero-Pest Zone System)', 'Evolve fertility management bait stations — reduces replacement colony formation'],
              ['Monitoring', 'Scheduled visit reports, Zero-Pest Zone Guarantee', 'Monthly track count plates — documented declining trend over 90 days'],
              ['Replacement cycle', 'Cleared by trapping, rebuilds 4–8 weeks later', 'Replacement population forms at reduced rate — density declines continuously'],
              ['DOHMH compliance record', 'Licensed PMP service documentation', 'Written monthly monitoring reports — 90-day trend line for inspectors'],
              ['Re-inspection risk', 'Dependent on inspection timing relative to last elimination', 'Reduced — documented declining population between visits'],
              ['Works with existing vendor', 'Is your existing vendor', 'Yes — Bell Environmental stays, Cloakd adds the fertility layer'],
            ].map(([feature, bell, cloakd]) => (
              <tr class="border-b border-[#1c1814]/8">
                <td class="py-4 pr-6 text-base font-semibold text-[#1c1814]">{feature}</td>
                <td class="py-4 pr-6 text-base text-[#1c1814]/60 leading-relaxed">{bell}</td>
                <td class="py-4 text-base text-[#1c1814]/70 leading-relaxed">{cloakd}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── FIELD DATA ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-[#f0ebe0]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        What fertility management adds to the outcome
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-12 max-w-2xl">
        Mechanical elimination plus fertility management. Different trajectory.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
        {[
          { value: '79%', label: 'reduction in rodent track presence', sub: 'Location A — 5-month urban building deployment, Aug 2025 to Jan 2026', color: '#7aab7e' },
          { value: '88%', label: 'drop in track density at the same site', sub: 'Tracks per monitoring plate declined even at stations with residual activity', color: '#7aab7e' },
          { value: '50%+', label: 'reduction at a second independent site', sub: 'Same 5-month period, different urban building profile', color: '#7aab7e' },
        ].map(({ value, label, sub, color }) => (
          <div class="bg-white border border-[#1c1814]/8 rounded-xl p-6">
            <p class="text-5xl font-bold mb-3" style={`color:${color}`}>{value}</p>
            <p class="text-base font-semibold text-[#1c1814] leading-snug mb-2">{label}</p>
            <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/60 leading-relaxed">{sub}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-[#1c1814]/40 max-w-2xl">
        Source: <a href="https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/senestech-reports-significant-reductions-in-rodent-activity-following-evolve-deployments-in-urban-field-studies-302691116.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-[#1c1814]/65 transition-colors">SenesTech, Inc. — February 18, 2026</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── WHO SHOULD USE EACH ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-[#c96a3a] text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-4">
        How to think about it
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-12 max-w-2xl">
        Bell handles elimination. Cloakd handles what comes after.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-[#f0ebe0] rounded-xl p-8">
          <p class="text-base font-semibold text-[#1c1814] mb-4">Bell Environmental alone is sufficient if:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            {[
              'You have a one-time infestation with no recurring citation history',
              'Your building doesn\'t have the surrounding density pressure driving fast replacement',
              'You need immediate elimination and licensed compliance documentation',
              'DOHMH inspection timing has consistently been favorable post-treatment',
            ].map((item) => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[#7aab7e] flex-shrink-0 mt-2"></div>
                <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/65">{item}</p>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-[#f0ebe0] rounded-xl p-8">
          <p class="text-base font-semibold text-[#1c1814] mb-4">Add Cloakd if:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            {[
              'You\'ve had repeat 04K or 04L citations despite consistent Bell service',
              'You need a documented 90-day population trend for DOHMH re-inspection',
              'The replacement cycle keeps resetting between scheduled visits',
              'Your inspector wants evidence of active management, not just elimination records',
            ].map((item) => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[#c96a3a]/50 flex-shrink-0 mt-2"></div>
                <p class="text-base text-[#1c1814]/65">{item}</p>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ─────────────────────────────────────── CTA ── -->
  <section class="py-24 px-6 bg-[#f0ebe0]">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="max-w-2xl">
        <h2 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1c1814] leading-tight mb-6">
          Bell Environmental handles elimination. The 90-day program handles what comes back.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg text-[#1c1814]/65 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          Tell us how long the cycle has been running and who handles
          your current service. We'll outline what the fertility layer
          adds on top.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
          <a
            href="/get-started"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-4 text-base font-semibold rounded bg-[#b85530] text-[#faf8f4] hover:bg-[#c96a3a] transition-colors"
          >
            Start the 90-day program
          </a>
          <a
            href="/why-it-keeps-coming-back"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-4 text-base font-medium rounded border border-[#1c1814]/15 text-[#1c1814]/70 hover:text-[#1c1814] hover:border-[#1c1814]/25 transition-colors"
          >
            Why it keeps coming back
          </a>
          <a
            href="/results"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-7 py-4 text-base font-medium rounded border border-[#1c1814]/15 text-[#1c1814]/70 hover:text-[#1c1814] hover:border-[#1c1814]/25 transition-colors"
          >
            Field data
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>
